Canada September 2023 Intake: Timeline, Universities & Admission Requirements

  • 3 min Read

Canada is one of the top study abroad destinations for Indian students. Apart from India, students from countries like China, Brazil, South Korea, Vietnam, the Philippines, and Mexico are also attracted by the quality of education that Canadian universities promise.

Studying in Canada after class 12th is the a dream of many Indian students. Students apply for different intakes to study their favourite program at a top university in Canada with guidance from study abroad consultants. Students with guidance from study abroad consultants apply for different intakes to study their favorite program at a top university in Canada. The three intakes in Canada are September/Fall intake, January/Winter intake, and May/Summer intake. In case you have missed the January and May intakes, you can apply for September intake.

Canada September 2023 Intake Timeline

To study in Canada, it is always best to start the application process a year early because it is a time taking process, and you are required to fulfil various academic and professional requirements to get admission to Canadian universities.

Here is a complete table with an outline to help you prepare for the September (2023) Intake:

Timeline For September Intake
Things to Do

April - August

Research and analyze the available study options

September - November

Prepare and attempt tests

November - January

Fill out application form

January - February

Reply to college email and responses

March - April

Settle your finances

Why apply for September intake Canada 2023?

September intake, or the Fall intake, is one of the most popular intakes in Canada because majority universities open slots for their popular programs in September intake.

Since it is the primary intake for admission with a higher acceptance rate, there is a higher chance of getting admission to your preferred institute. The September intake allows you to start your new academic year just a few months after your term completion in India. The timeline for this intake is from September to August next year, which allows you to choose and apply from a range of bachelor's and master's degrees and other courses. You have around 3-4 months to apply to your desired university in Canada. The application deadline for this intake ends in December.

Step-by-Step Guide to Apply for Canada Universities September Intake

Below is a step-by-step guide to apply for Canadian universities for the September intake to ensure a smooth and successful application process.

1.Shortlist your preferred universities: Research and shortlist universities in Canada that offer your program of interest.

2.Check admission requirements: Check the admission requirements of the university. The general admission requirements are providing academic transcripts, proof of English language proficiency test, recommendation letters, a statement of purpose, and other documents, depending on the university and program you are applying to.

3.Prepare your documents: Collect and arrange all the required documents for the application process, which includes academic transcripts, standardized test scores, recommendation letters, and statement of purpose.

4.Apply to the selected university: Apply to the selected program in your preferred university and submit all the required documents before the application deadline.

5.Wait for the Acceptance Letter: You will need to wait for the university's decision. Check emails regularly and revert timely.

6.Accept admission offer: After receiving an acceptance letter from the university, you must accept the admission offer and confirm your enrolment.

7.Apply for Canada Student Visa: Now, you have to apply for Canada student visa by providing acceptance letter, proof of financial support and other documents.

8.Book flight tickets- Book your flight tickets and embark on your new journey.

Fall Intake in Canada 2023 Benefits

Fall/September is the most popular intake for international students to study in Canada 2023.
 
•More program options are available and the acceptance rate is high in Fall intake.

•September intake is the primary intake due to which many universities and colleges offer various scholarship opportunities to students.

•The fall intake is the beginning of the academic year in Canada and students can network with peers and professionals.

•Fall in Canada is known for its pleasant weather, making it a great time to explore and enjoy outdoor activities.

Documents required to study in September 2023 Intake in Canada Universities

You need a few documents to apply to the universities in Canada. As it is the primary intake, there is a lot of competition, so it is best to apply early and with all the required documents to get your offer letter easily. A completed application form contains:

  • Academic certificates and transcripts
  • CV
  • Passport
  • Recommendation letter
  • English proficiency certificate
  • Statement of Purpose
  • Experience letter
  • Certificate of extracurricular activities (if any)
  • Proof of financial support

FAQ

When should I apply for fall intake in Canada 2023?

The fall intake in Canada starts in September. It is best to begin the application process in April of the previous year and continue till August. You can research colleges and courses you can apply to during this time.

Which intake is best for Canada 2023?

September intake is one of the most preferred intakes in Canada, as all the top universities open slots for their popular courses in this intake. If you plan to study in Canada as soon as you complete your course in India, September is the best intake, as the academic year in India ends just before September.

When should I give IELTS for the September intake?

It is always best to take the TOEFL/ IELTS a year before the intake. You can register for these tests a month before.

What is the deadline for September intake Canada?

The Deadline for the September 2023 admissions intake is between January and February. It is always better to check the specific university deadline and submit the application in advance.

Why should you choose a study abroad Consultant to study in Canada?

Study abroad Consultants like Canam has partnerships with some of the most prestigious universities abroad and help students seek easy admission to their favourite university. The study abroad counsellors help students select the right program/University that promises a rewarding Career.
